{{BLP sources|date=April 2012}}
'''Paul Mattick Jr.''' (born 1944) is a [[Marxist]] theorist and philosopher.
He is the son of [[council communist]] theoreticians [[Paul Mattick|Paul Mattick Sr.]] (1904-1981) and Ilse Mattick (1919-2009).
Mattick was involved in the council communist group Root and Branch, which sporadically published a magazine/pamphlet series, starting in 1969. Other notable members include [[Jeremy Brecher]], [[Stanley Aronowitz]], and [[Peter Rachleff]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Root and Branch Archive |url=//www.labor.iu.edu/LaborHistory/rab/home.html |accessdate=11 April 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041028192535/http://www.labor.iu.edu/LaborHistory/rab/home.html |archivedate=October 28, 2004 |df= }}</ref><ref name="Root and Branch">{{cite book |last=Root and Branch|first=Ed.|title=Root and Branch: The Rise of the Workers' Movements|year=1975|publisher=Fawcett Publications |location=Greenwich, Conn.}}</ref>
Mattick obtained his [[PhD]] from [[Harvard]] in 1981. He was previously the editor of the ''International Journal of Political Economy'', and is the author of several books on [[philosophy of language]], [[aesthetics]], and the [[critique of political economy]].
==Key works== *''Social Knowledge: An Essay on the Nature and Limits of Social Science'' (1986) *''Art in Its Time: Theories and Practices of Modern Aesthetics'' (2003) *''Eighteenth-Century Aesthetics and the Reconstruction of Art'' (editor) (2008) *''Business as Usual: The Economic Crisis and the Failure of Capitalism'' (2011)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsocialism.org/spgb/socialist-standard/2010s/2011/no-1281-may-2011/book-review-business-usual-economic-crisis-and-failur|title=Book Review : "Business As Usual: The Economic Crisis And The Failure Of Capitalism"|last=Watkins|first=Stuart|date=May 2011|publisher=Socialist Standard|accessdate=28 April 2012}}</ref>
